  abstract = {A technique involving eddy current heating has been used to study the Sondheimer oscillations in the resistivity of single crystal discs of indium. Oscillations were observed for magnetic fields in all directions in the (001), (100), and (110) crystallographic planes. With a few exceptions the oscillation periods agree to better than 5% with those arising from orbits in the second zone of a Fermi surface model which has been proposed on the basis of de Haas-van Alphen data. The field dependence of the oscillation amplitudes have been measured, and large discrepancies with the simple theory were found.},
